title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson M&P40c (with LaserLyte S.C. V2)
postcontent:
Smith & Wesson M&P40c (with LaserLyte S.C. V2)

I have for sale a Smith & Wesson M&P40c in excellent condition.  This gun is chambered for .40 S&W and is the compact version of Smith & Wesson's very popular M&P line of polymer pistols.  I am including a LaserLyte S.C. V2, a high quality rail-mounted laser that fits the short rail of the M&P40c.

The Smith & Wesson M&P40c is in excellent condition.  There have only been about 100 rounds fired through the pistol; all quality, factory ammunition.  The gun was purchased new by me and hasn't had any previous owners.  The gun has been kept cleaned and oiled per the factory recommendations.  The gun was only used at the range and therefore has no holster wear, rust, or other problems.  It functions flawlessly.  The gun comes with two factory 10-round magazines: one that is flush with the pistol (allowing for two fingers on the grip) and one that has a small extension (allowing for three fingers on the grip), just as all M&P compact pistols.  Also included is the original manual and original lockable gun case.  This specific model is configured with a thumb safety, no magazine safety, and no internal lock.  The gun is factory stock with no modifications or aftermarket parts.

The LaserLyte S.C. V2 rail-mounted laser is a quality laser with a factory MSRP of $99.95.  The laser is built specifically for subcompact pistols with a short rail.  The batteries (three 393-style batteries) will need to be replaced; included are batteries that still function, but are running low.  Included with the laser are the original two hex wrenches (for adjusting the laser and removing the batteries), an optional Picatinny rail mount (that can be added to the bottom to allow another accessory to be mounted underneath the laser, such as a light), and the original two mounting screws (to mount the optional Picatinny rail mount).  Original instructions are not included; however, printed copies from the official website are included.

Asking price is $500 OBO.  I am looking primarily for cash; however, I will consider trading if it involves a GLOCK 22 Gen4, GLOCK 23 Gen4, or GLOCK 35 Gen4.   Preferred method of sale is face to face in person.  I am located in Winter Garden, near Ocoee.  If shipping is required, the cost must be covered by the buyer.

A firearms bill of sale is required; no exceptions.  Florida ID is also required (driver's  license, state ID, and/or concealed weapon license).

If you have any questions please feel free to contact me.  I am available to reply quickly at almost all times.

[ Tags: S&W M&P 40c .40 compact military&police military & police Smith&Wesson handgun ]

title: For Sale/Trade:  MAKAROV PISTOL GENTLY USED WITH LOT'S OF EXTRAS! L@@K!!!
postcontent: FS: 1  Bulgarian Makarov semiautomatic pistol chambered in 9x18 Mak.  This pistol will only fire 9 x18  MAKAROV ammo. Using any other ammo caliber in this pistol such as .380acp, or 9x18 police ultra can cause serious injury to the user!  This pistol is a police surplus pistol before it was imported and therefore has some minor holster wear but is in perfect functioning order and is in good cosmetic condition as well. The Makarov  model pistol was  once the standard sidearm for the Soviet military and police as well as used by the KGB, East German Stasi and military forces in Eastern Europe and around the world.  During the cold war the Makarov was produced in East Germany, Bulgaria, and Russia.  Sometimes called the "AK-47" of pistols, this pistol is known for superb reliability and simplicity that is the hallmark of Soviet era gun design.  During the war between the Soviets and the CIA backed Mujahideen in Afghanistan during the 1980s the Makarov was prized much as an iPHONE is today.  If you had one, you were one of the "cool" guys.  With the fall of the Soviet Union large numbers of these pistols made there way to US shores through importers of surplus arms.   Once rare war trophy bring backs from war zones like Vietnam and Afghanistan, these days  any legal gun owner can purchase a piece of history!  The Mak. is similar to the Walther PPK in size and power, with a  simpler design and fewer parts. This blued, solid  steel, fixxed barrel, blowback pistol is FUN to shoot!  Very accurate within 20 or 30 yards.  It will shoot any brand of ammo I have tried from expensive brass cased Hornady to cheaper stuff like Brown Bear and I have never had a jam or misfired once after shooting at least 7 kinds of ammo from brass to steel case HP and FMJ. Take down and cleaning is easy and replacement parts are plentiful and cheap! The Makarov can be converted to fire more readily available .380ACP by changing the barrel.  If you change the barrel to .380ACP you can use the same magazine due to .380 an 9x18 being similar size.  Those looking for a suitable gun for concealed carry should consider buying this pistol.   The  Makarov  makes a great concealed carry pistol due to its small size and thin profile thanks in part to using a sing stack magazine, keeping the width of the pistol down.   Once used for plain clothes police work in Eastern Europe   The Mak lends itself well to concealed carry.  The pistol, carried in a pants, or jacket pocket does not 'print' very much and is easy to draw.  When firing,  the all steel construction makes felt recoil  low for a small pocket sized semi auto.  The trigger guard is large enough to fit a gloved finger, a nice feature on a small framed pistol. The safety system consists of a decocker that blocks the firing pin from striking the bullet.  Some people do not use the decocker at all and simply carry the pistol with a round chambered, safety off like a DAO style pistol or revolver.  The decocker doubles as the safety.  When the safety is in the up position, it  decocks the hammer if it is cocked, the firing pin is blocked and the trigger cannot be pulled.  Push the safety lever down and you can now actuate the trigger and fire the weapon.  When you go to shoot the pistol the first shot is double action, with each subsequent shot  being single action.  The double action pull for the first round can be avoided by simply  cocking the exposed hammer prior to firing.  The double action trigger pull is long but not bad for a stock trigger.  The single action trigger pull is pretty good as well. After firing the last round the slide is held open by the slide lock and magazines are changed with a european style heel mag release. Mags drop free easily, making reloading in a hostile situation easier.  Mag release is somewhat small, but adding a split ring or a short lanyard can make changing mags faster. Most surplus single stack Makarov pistols for sale online come with 1 or perhaps 2 magazines included at the MOST (if they even offer the option of a second magazine at all)....  The pistol I am selling will include 3 single stack magazines, with 2 mags in excellent condition ( Single stack Makarov mags are  somewhat hard to find for sale and cost about 30 bucks a piece when they can be found).  Also included in the sale will be 3 50 round box of HP and FMJ Brown and Silver Bear ammunition, as well as a genuine leather Makarov tactical retaining lanyard.  The pistol comes with two sets of grips.  The standard issue red grips as well as black wraparound grips.  To purchase the gun from a dealer with all these accessories  you would spend well  over 300 dollars!  The firearm itself has minor holster wear as well as some minimal wear around the slide catch.  If you are a collector of Comm Blocc weaponry buy this pistol.  If you are a CCW holder looking for a reliable DA/SA pistol that will go bang when you pull the trigger EVERY single time but don't want to carry a plastic gun buy this pistol.  If you are a female shooter who doesn't want a gun with a lot of recoil and muzzle flip but still want the stopping power of a medium sized round buy this pistol.  If you already own a Makarov and want a spare Makarov for parts and spare magazines buy this pistol.  If you own a CZ-82 or a PA-63 and want to add a "REAL" Makarov to your collection this is the pistol for you.  Whether used for concealed carry or just looking for a low priced gun with a lot of features this is a great pistol for just about anyone looking for a low priced gun with all the features of an expensive Walther PPK costing over 500.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ohio CCW Course (Small classes = one on one attention!)
postcontent:
Course is 12 hours long by state law.  Price is $125 and includes all course materials, lunch at Jason's Deli, range time, and .22 rental w/ ammo if you do not already own a handgun.  You are welcome to bring your own handgun, please bring 75 to 100 rounds of ammunition with it.  Class is split between 10 hours of class time and 2 hours of range time.

Classes are kept below a maximum of 6 students to ensure adequate instructor/student time, but there is no minimum class size.  This class teaches the skills, mindset, and knowledge that may someday save your life.  DON'T SETTLE FOR A CLASS OF 20 STUDENTS TO SAVE A FEW BUCKS!

We cover Gun control/2nd amendment history, firearm/ammunition basics, the Hollywood myths of what bullets will and will not do, shooting fundamentals, Sheepdog mindset, physiological effects of combat, surviving gunshots, the "how to's" and "considerations" of concealed carry, and of course Ohio laws and the justified use of lethal force.

Group prices are available for couples or larger groups.

AUGUST AND SEPTEMBER CLASSES ARE FILLING FAST!
